{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11",
    "summary": "Source text for 4 Maccabees 11 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:1",
      "text": "And when he had died, disfigured in his torments, the fifth leaped forward, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:2",
      "text": "I intend not, O tyrant, to get excused from the torment which is in behalf of virtue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:3",
      "text": "But I have come of mine own accord, that by the death of me, you may owe heavenly vengeance a punishment for more crimes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:4",
      "text": "O thou hater of virtue and of men, what have we done that thou thus revellest in our blood?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:5",
      "text": "Does it seem evil to thee that we worship the Founder of all things, and live according to his surpassing law?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:6",
      "text": "But this is worthy of honours, not torments;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:7",
      "text": "hadst thou been capable of the higher feelings of men, and possessed the hope of salvation from God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:8",
      "text": "Behold now, being alien from God, thou makest war against those who are religious toward God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:9",
      "text": "As he said this, the spearbearers bound him, and drew him to the catapelt:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:10",
      "text": "to which binding him at his knees, and fastening them with iron fetters, they bent down his loins upon the wedge of the wheel; and his body was then dismembered, scorpion-fashion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:11",
      "text": "With his breath thus confined, and his body strangled, he said,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:12",
      "text": "A great favour thou bestowest upon us, O tyrant, by enabling us to manifest our adherence to the law by means of nobler sufferings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:13",
      "text": "He also being dead, the sixth, quite a youth, was brought out; and on the tyrant asking him whether he would eat and be delivered, he said,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:14",
      "text": "I am indeed younger than my brothers, but in understanding I am am as old;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:15",
      "text": "for having been born and reared unto the same end, we are bound to die also in behalf of the same cause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:16",
      "text": "So that if ye think proper to torment us for not eating the unclean;--torment!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:17",
      "text": "As he said this, they brought him to the wheel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:18",
      "text": "Extended upon which, with limbs racked and dislocated, he was gradually roasted from beneath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:19",
      "text": "And having heated sharp spits, they approached them to his back; and having transfixed his sides, they burned away his entrails.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:20",
      "text": "And he, while tormented, said, O period good and holy, in which, for the sake of religion, we brethren have been called to the contest of pain, and have not been conquered.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:21",
      "text": "For religious understanding, O tyrant, is unconquered.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:22",
      "text": "Armed with upright virtue, I also shall depart with my brethren.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:23",
      "text": "I, too, bearing with me a great avenger, O deviser of tortures, and enemy of the truly pious.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:24",
      "text": "We six youths have destroyed thy tyranny.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:25",
      "text": "For is not your inability to overrule our reasoning, and to compel us to eat the unclean, thy destruction?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:26",
      "text": "Your fire is cold to us, your catapelts are painless, and your violence harmless.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.11.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 11:27",
      "text": "For the guards not of a tyrant but of a divine law are our defenders: through this we keep our reasoning unconquered.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
